About Small Kitchen Appliances

Small appliances can be any kind of household gadget that helps your day go more smoothly. Small kitchen appliances save time, and depending on what small appliances youre using, they can help you save money as well.

While small kitchen appliances like toasters and coffeemakers are considered almost indispensable to most homeowners, appliances like dehydrators, air fryers and rice cookers can help people broaden their cooking skills and save time in the kitchen. Carefully selected kitchen electronics and countertop appliances also make excellent gifts for newlyweds and housewarmings.

Know Which Small Appliances You Really Need

In order to decide which small appliances you really cant live without, you should take into account your daily habits and your unique interests. Before you commit to purchasing small kitchen appliances like countertop microwaves, its important to consider the amount of counter space or cabinet storage space you can designate for your new appliance.

If you love to cook but dont have a lot of extra counter space to work with, you may want to consider adding small cooking appliances like electric pressure cookers that can be easily stored away.

Choosing the Right Small Appliances

Small kitchen electronics make it easy to prepare a wide range of food and drinks. Consider these essential kitchen countertop appliances.

Coffee Machines: Wake up to a freshly brewed pot of coffee or use your single-serve coffee machine for an afternoon pick-me-up. Choose coffee carafes for all-day coffee drinkers and espresso machines for a fresh cup on demand. If youre a tea drinker, electric kettles heat water quickly to the perfect temperature and shut off automatically for your safety.

Multi-Cookers: Save time and energy in the kitchen by letting slow cookers and multi-cookers do all the heavy lifting. With multiple cooking programs and heat settings, these versatile cookers make easy work of large roasts, stews, soups and so much more.

Blenders and Food Processors: If you love smoothies, milkshakes and soups, you should add a freestanding or handheld immersion blender to your kitchen lineup. These small kitchen appliances are great for making that delicious breakfast smoothie or a hot pot of soup when the weather gets cold.

If youd prefer something even more versatile, however, a food processor with multiple settings can quickly chop or mince herbs, produce and more.

Toasters: Quickly toast your morning bagel with a basic toaster, or warm up leftovers for dinner with a toaster oven. Toaster ovens are also great for heating up pizza so it has that crispy taste like when it was first made.

Specialty Appliances

Use specialty appliances like deep fryers and yogurt makers for a treats and special occasions. Some are small enough to easily store in kitchen cabinets. If you love popcorn, our vintage popcorn machines drum up nostalgia and will be the talk of your house guests. For hosting a gathering, choose food warmers and chafing dishes to keep your offerings at the perfect temperature.
